# DESIGN-RULES.md is the single source of truth for UI rules

When editing any file matched by the globs above, you MUST obey [DESIGN-RULES.md](../../DESIGN-RULES.md). Specifically:

- **No Tailwind on Shadcn instances** for color / border / shadow / typography / radius / internal padding (§2). Page-layout classes are fine.
- **No browser dialogs** (`alert`, `confirm`, `prompt`) — use Sonner toasts or `<AlertDialog>` (§3).
- **Prioritize Shadcn primitives** over raw `<div>` blocks when one exists (§4).
- **No Tailwind on icons inside `<Button>`** (§5).
- **Every screen works in light AND dark mode** (§6).
- **`<EmptyState>` is mandatory** for any list/grid/table that can be empty (§7).
- **No hardcoded palettes / shadows / fonts / inline styles** for visual props (§8).
- **No redundant subtitle / `<description>`** — skip when title is enough (§9.1, §9.2).
- **Button labels: single infinitive verb** (§10).
- **Feedback messages: past-tense success, direct error** (§11).
- **Data screens handle 4 states**: loading (`<Skeleton>`), error (`<Alert variant="destructive">`), empty (`<EmptyState>`), success (§12).
- **All user-facing strings through `t()`** (§14).
- **Primary actions inside footer blocks** of Card / Dialog / Sheet / Drawer (§13).

When unsure, re-read the relevant DESIGN-RULES.md section before writing the code.
